Clinicians' time is valuable–and much of that time is consumed in EMR tasks. Headquarters Regions: Greater Chicago Area, Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: The mission of Variety Children’s Charities is to provide funding and services for programs that strive to alleviate suffering and improve the quality of life for children who are mentally and physically challenged, abused, sick, homeless or underprivileged.  Variety the Children’s Charity believes every child deserves access to lead a full, active life. Through an array of programs and fundraising endeavors, Variety of Illinois helps to give children with disabilities the freedom and independence to live life and fulfill their roles in society.  Variety of Illinois receives no government funding. We currently support a number of programs through special events, corporate sponsorships and underwriting as well as private and corporate donations.  Variety the Children’s Charity is dedicated to promoting and protecting the health and wellbeing of children. Through a network of 54 chapters in 14 countries, Variety reaches into communities across the globe to offer financial assistance and services to children and organizations that serve children with disabilities. Through hard work, thoughtful stewardship and single-minded focus on the needs of the young, Variety strives to make a lasting difference in the lives of children, their families, our communities and the world…one need at a time.  The U.S chapters of Variety – The Children’s Charity are a multi-million dollar philanthropic organization with locations throughout the United States. Beginning with a baby left on the doorsteps of a movie theater in 1928, professional men and women, many from the theater and film industry, have been helping children in need. Today, through the efforts of our enthusiastic volunteers and generous corporate contributors, we remain true to our heritage by giving children real, tangible help.

Description: Trinity Energy Group is actively engaged in oil, gas and energy opportunities in North America, Central America and Worldwide.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Los Angeles Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Trinity Energy Group Inc. (“TEG” or “the Company”), a Nevada corporation headquartered in Irvine, California, is actively engaged in oil, gas and energy opportunities in North America, Central America and Worldwide. TEG’s scope of activity ranges from due-diligence for potential investments through development, supervision and management of drilling and production operations, oversight and management of investments, and execution of exit strategies for existing projects.  Trinity has assembled a team of seasoned experts with industry expertise and core-competencies to manage the investment life-cycle from project acquisition through development, drilling, production and exit strategy for investor liquidity of each project and investment.                                                                                                                      (The Kelly Lease) The Kelly lease is approximately 40 acres in size and is located in Bakersfield Ca.  The interest to be acquired is 70% Working Interest (WI) and 56% Net Revenue Interest (NRI) and the lease contains approximately 6.7 million gross barrels of oil (mbo) in place (which equates to approximately 4.0 million barrels of oil recoverable) in five different producing zones of the China Grade formation which can be produced by a steam flood operation. Some 15 wells were drilled in the 1940’s and ‘50’s and were produced for a time. However, when oil prices plunged in the mid to late 1990’s, the operation became uneconomic and the operator of that time simply abandoned the field. The California Department of Oil and Gas assumed operations and performed abandonment procedures on the existing wells in 2002, which left most of the downhole piping in place. We believe that we can utilize these wells to serve as production wells but new steam injection wells will need to be drilled and equipped.

Description: Kerr Ingram in 1988 I wanted the company
Full Description: When I founded Kerr Ingram in 1988 I wanted the company to be different from and, frankly, better than other executive search consultancies operating in the UK market. I did not want to grow a huge business operating across all sectors, because I knew that the only way to provide a genuinely well-informed and highly professional service was to specialise in just one sector. By concentrating exclusively on the property sector for the past twenty years, I have been able to get to know the industry exceptionally well. This not only informs the all-important identification of the best performers, it is also crucial to the interview and reporting process. Unlike other professions, property specialists often have the same basic training and qualifications, but differ vastly in skill base, ability, depth of knowledge, creative drive, contacts and industry standing. By knowing the sector so well, I understand fully how to select the very best, and most appropriate, candidates for any given role.

Description: Seahorse Chocolate is honestly and thoughtfully crafted single origin chocolate in Bend, Oregon.
Full Description: Seahorse Chocolate is a single-origin cocoa roaster located in Bend, OR. Our philosophy is simple, work closely with farmers, tailor roast each small batch to reveal hidden nuances, and hand wrap distinct varietals into delicious chocolate bars. One taste and you will recognize why we are one of a kind. We are roasters, that's what we do, and cocoa, like wine and coffee, contains layered flavors that vary greatly depending on the region, soil, altitude, farmer, and preparation. Roasting for each varietal requires meticulous skill in order to reveal these unique aspects. Our goal is to inspire appreciation for single-origin cocoa.

CourseWeaver’s™ unique approach is based on the patented Michigan State University LON-CAPA global platform - by educators for educators. The LON-CAPA system has hosted over a million students for hundreds of institutions across nine countries and continues to support hundreds of thousands of students yearly. CourseWeaver’s™ global platform is a new design, driven by the needs and feedback of a coalition of LON-CAPA users from leading US and international universities and K-12 schools. CourseWeaver™ seamlessly combines a cutting-edge Learning Management and CourseBuilder System, and Education Content channel, bridging both with our Marketplace and Content Authoring Tools. This unites and integrates the supply, delivery, and management of education content and instruction. CourseWeaver™ allows independents, authors, and professors to publish and sell granular educational content alongside commercial publishers and free, open-source materials, within a new integrated global marketplace – empowering instructors to share, sell and use the best resources available globally. Headquartered in East Lansing, Michigan’s growing tech corridor near MSU, CourseWeaver’s™ culture embodies innovation and creativity, delivering products that are both beautiful and easy to use.
Industry Groups: Content and Publishing, Education, Internet Services, Media and Entertainment, Software
Founders: Gerd Kortemeyer, Robert Fulk, Wolfgang Bauer
